Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.97,0:00:02.64,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,In the year 845...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.98,0:00:06.12,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,the Colossal and Armored Titans
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.12,0:00:09.78,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,suddenly appeared, destroying the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.78,0:00:11.64,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,along with the life we'd known.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.80,0:00:17.27,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And the insatiable hunger of the Titans \Nwas unleashed on humanity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.66,0:00:19.91,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,after a hundred years of deprivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.12,0:00:23.79,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.05,0:00:26.49,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity abandoned Wall Maria,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.17,0:00:30.67,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,losing twenty percent of its population \Nand a third of its territory,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.07,0:00:34.76,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,to retreat within Wall Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.98,0:02:14.98,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Night of the Graduation Ceremony \NHumanity Rises Again (2)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.36,0:02:18.70,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(523,416)}The Year: 850
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.91,0:02:22.28,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(223,345)}2 Years After Enlistment
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.45,0:02:22.57,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,You're too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.57,0:02:24.33,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Run, you laggards!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.16,0:02:27.58,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Arlert?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.41,0:02:29.37,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,You're falling behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.88,0:02:32.79,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Is it too heavy for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.79,0:02:34.50,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be the one guy to remove his equipment?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.17,0:02:39.59,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,If this were a real fight, \Nyou'd be Titan food by now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.84,0:02:42.85,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.85,0:02:44.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Give me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.39,0:02:48.14,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, we'll all fail out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.65,0:02:50.56,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We're being graded on this exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:54.27,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,If you do that, you'll lose points, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.27,0:02:55.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Just don't let them find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.09,0:02:58.28,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And don't make me change my mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.45,0:03:02.95,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Reiner Braun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.95,0:03:07.83,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,A strong soldier, physically and mentally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.83,0:03:10.21,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,And trusted by his comrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.97,0:03:15.34,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,I will not slow everyone down, even if it kills me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.99,0:03:22.48,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Armin Arlert.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:24.76,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,While lacking in physical strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.76,0:03:26.97,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,he's demonstrated an \Nextraordinary aptitude for his studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.61,0:03:45.87,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Annie Leonhart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.53,0:03:48.66,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Her strike form is flawless,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.66,0:03:51.05,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but she works poorly with others \Nand tends to isolate herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.87,0:03:53.47,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Bertolt Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.47,0:03:57.00,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,He has great potential, but lacks initiative.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.84,0:03:59.09,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Jean Kirschstein.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.67,0:04:01.67,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,A master of 3D Maneuver Gear,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.67,0:04:05.03,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,but his brash personality causes \Nfriction with the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.60,0:04:09.56,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,I can't strike as hard as those two,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.02,0:04:12.02,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,so I'll have to find the Titan first!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.94,0:04:18.12,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be the one who makes \Nit into the Military Police!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.87,0:04:23.15,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.51,0:04:26.87,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,I was right to follow you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.65,0:04:34.96,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Sasha Blause.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.27,0:04:37.46,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,She has unconventional, good instincts,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.46,0:04:39.92,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but they make her unsuited to teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:42.60,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Connie Springer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.60,0:04:47.43,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,He demonstrates superior physical agility, \Nbut lacks mental agility.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:48.68,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,They're coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.18,0:04:58.10,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.10,0:04:59.73,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,Mikasa's beat me again in strike depth!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.49,0:05:01.81,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Mikasa Ackerman.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.18,0:05:04.68,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,A master of all subjects,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.68,0:05:08.00,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and widely considered \None of the best in our history.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.78,0:05:10.12,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,Eren Jaeger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.49,0:05:12.08,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,He has no outstanding talents,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.08,0:05:14.54,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but he's worked harder than \Nanyone to improve his marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:19.07,Default - italics,K,0000,0000,0000,,And he is more motivated to \Nattain his goal than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.70,0:05:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.15,0:05:41.06,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I'm not good at holding back...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.90,0:05:45.38,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's your turn to be the bandit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.86,0:05:48.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.80,0:05:50.87,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point of this training?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.03,0:05:54.37,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Why are soldiers training \Nto fight people like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:05:58.67,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Only an idiot would fight an opponent unarmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.22,0:06:03.17,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Where's your sense of responsibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:05.71,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We're soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We may be called on to fight at a severe disadvantage, \Nand retreat will not be an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.50,0:06:12.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We must be able to handle any opponent,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whether that means using \Na cannon or martial arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.93,0:06:20.52,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That is our responsibility as soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.65,0:06:24.34,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Forget all that... Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.38,0:06:28.07,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Annie?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:32.20,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,As usual, she's good at slacking off \Nwithout getting found out by the instructor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.53,0:06:33.83,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Eren...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:36.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I think that slacker needs a lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.40,0:06:40.25,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Let us show her what a soldier should strive to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:47.42,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want the instructor to \Nheadbutt you again, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:50.60,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't want to get any shorter,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.60,0:06:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,remember what happened when you \Ncame here, and take this seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.80,0:06:55.80,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, isn't that a little harsh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.23,0:07:00.60,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,She's really mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.03,0:07:03.15,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,I always thought she was scary looking,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.69,0:07:05.90,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,but she's way worse when she's really mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.44,0:07:08.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get going, Eren.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.32,0:07:09.36,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.83,0:07:17.95,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Annie, you know how to do this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:19.20,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.84,0:07:25.71,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.17,0:07:27.46,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Did she kick my leg?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.93,0:07:30.30,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Can I go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.51,0:07:33.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, this drill doesn't end \Nuntil you grab the dagger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.43,0:07:36.69,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.69,0:07:38.52,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You're supposed to do this a certain way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.54,0:07:47.48,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.98,0:07:51.53,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's your turn to attack me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.15,0:07:54.11,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.11,0:07:55.28,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, Reiner...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.31,0:07:59.79,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you going to teach her \Na soldier's responsibilities?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.54,0:08:04.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.84,0:08:06.96,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, a soldier can't retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.50,0:08:09.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Like now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.39,0:08:17.38,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,That was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.38,0:08:18.98,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you learn that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.85,0:08:21.23,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My father.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.23,0:08:22.85,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Your dad taught you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.85,0:08:24.10,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:27.69,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't any point in doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.23,0:08:29.86,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You mean this exercise?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.78,0:08:33.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Martial arts won't improve your score.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:36.53,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You should just go through \Nthe motions, like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.28,0:08:40.66,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones allowed to join the Military \NPolice and go deep within the walls
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are those who rank in the final top ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.98,0:08:45.54,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The only ones who take this seriously
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are either people like you, \Nwho do whatever they're told,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.77,0:08:49.98,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,or real idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.17,0:08:52.34,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, the instructor...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:57.47,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,For whatever reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.47,0:09:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the better equipped you are to fight Titans,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.07,0:09:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the farther you're assigned from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.60,0:09:04.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you think this farce begins?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.39,0:09:07.52,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.40,0:09:16.16,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it because that is how humans really are?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.83,0:09:24.26,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm not stupid enough
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.87,0:09:30.13,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,to enjoy playing soldiers in this shitty world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.47,0:09:35.84,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't cut out to be a soldier at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.64,0:09:41.42,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,I was so focused on getting stronger, \NI never even realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.97,0:09:43.77,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,such an obvious contradiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.85,0:09:47.90,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,They're honing their Titan-killing skills
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.90,0:09:50.27,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,so that they'll never need to fight them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.43,0:09:56.53,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.28,0:09:59.91,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Before Wall Maria fell,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.91,0:10:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only the few in the Survey Corps needed \Nto know how to use Maneuver Gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.91,0:10:06.71,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,To save the knowledge base from decline,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.29,0:10:07.25,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Just give it one strong blast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.71,0:10:08.93,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,they used the Interior to motivate...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.25,0:10:10.96,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Use the generated momentum, \Nand you'll conserve fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.38,0:10:13.21,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You make it sound so easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.21,0:10:16.67,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess not everyone can do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.47,0:10:20.39,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,But it's worth remembering.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:22.81,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to join the Military Police, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.81,0:10:25.24,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I hope I can get in...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.62,0:10:29.38,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine a greater honor \Nthan serving near the King.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.77,0:10:30.77,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Marco.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.56,0:10:35.23,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Cut the noble act and tell the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.61,0:10:37.44,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,You want to join the Military Police
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.44,0:10:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because life deep inside \Nthe walls is soft and easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.07,0:10:43.14,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No! I really think that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.14,0:10:44.62,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,An easy life, deep inside the walls?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.20,0:10:49.54,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Until five years ago, this was \Nconsidered deep inside the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.37,0:10:53.00,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,What's your point, Eren?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.42,0:10:57.06,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to go to the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.76,0:11:00.13,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You've gone soft enough in your own head.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.60,0:11:04.35,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.72,0:11:06.56,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's strange
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.27,0:11:11.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that we're training to fight Titans, \Njust to end up farther from them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.86,0:11:13.77,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.77,0:11:16.73,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,For my own sake, I hope they \Nkeep this stupid system.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.57,0:11:18.75,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You piece of shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.75,0:11:20.61,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! This is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.61,0:11:21.99,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Eren.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.41,0:11:23.49,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.50,0:11:29.92,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Screw you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.16,0:11:31.98,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Let go! My clothes will rip!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.98,0:11:33.42,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares about your clothes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.42,0:11:34.00,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so envious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.00,0:11:35.79,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.68,0:11:45.90,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, he...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.81,0:11:49.22,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,He is who I used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.87,0:11:51.90,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,A ranting idiot with no control.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.32,0:11:53.65,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm different now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:11:59.19,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use what I've learned \Nto handle this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.98,0:12:11.54,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.08,0:12:16.34,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,The martial arts I went through a world of hurt \Nto learn while you were screwing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.63,0:12:21.59,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You think taking the easy way out, \Ndoing as you please, is reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:24.02,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,And you can call yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.01,0:12:26.18,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,a soldier?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.16,0:12:38.32,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I heard quite a commotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.63,0:12:41.07,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Would someone like to explain?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.26,0:12:48.70,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,That sound was Sasha's fart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.99,0:12:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.03,0:12:51.20,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,You again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:55.21,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Learn to control yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.84,0:13:09.79,Default - italics,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, two hundred and eighteen trainees \Nmanaged to hang on till graduation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.85,0:13:14.31,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Dedicate your hearts!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.27,0:13:21.78,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Today, you trainee graduates \Nwill be given three choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.48,0:13:26.16,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,You can join the Garrison, \Nprotecting towns and reinforcing the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.55,0:13:30.87,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Or the Survey Corps, who risk their lives \Nbeyond the walls, in Titan territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.20,0:13:35.75,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Or the Military Police, who serve the King, \Nlead the people, and protect internal order.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.25,0:13:38.71,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, only the top ten students,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.29,0:13:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whose names were just announced \Ncan join the Military Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.95,0:13:51.01,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,I finally made it this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.22,0:13:53.60,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's our turn
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.56,0:13:56.52,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,to devour the Titans!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.94,0:14:03.94,Eyecatch1,,0000,0000,0000,,Information We Can Share So Far: \N\NTop 10 Scores, 104th Trainee Corps \N\N10) Krista Lenz \N9) Sasha Blause \N8) Connie Springer \N7) Marco Bott \N6) Jean Kirschstein
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.94,0:14:09.95,Eyecatch2,,0000,0000,0000,,Information We Can Share So Far: \N\NTop 10 Scores, 104th Trainee Corps \N\N5) Eren Jaeger \N4) Annie Leonhart \N3) Bertolt Hoover \N2) Reiner Braun \N1) Mikasa Ackerman
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.56,0:14:14.42,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.42,0:14:16.02,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joining the Military Police!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.02,0:14:18.19,Default,Sa,0000,0000,0000,,We won't go hungry anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.25,0:14:21.80,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,How did I score lower than Eren?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.26,0:14:23.20,Default,J,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.19,0:14:27.12,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,You seriously aren't joining \Nthe Military Police, Eren?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.12,0:14:29.58,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,You did all that work to make the top ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.20,0:14:32.01,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I'd already decided when I began.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.67,0:14:35.98,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't training to live in the Interior.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:38.42,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I was training to fight Titans.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.82,0:14:40.23,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,You'll never beat them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.46,0:14:45.98,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,You do know how many
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.57,0:14:48.32,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,tens of thousands have been eaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.86,0:14:51.99,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,We lost over twenty percent of our \Npopulation, so we know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.42,0:14:56.80,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,Humans cannot defeat Titans.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.02,0:15:04.02,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.00,0:15:08.13,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,If you think we can't win, you'll just give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.47,0:15:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.09,0:15:13.10,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that humanity has \Nonly suffered defeat until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.74,0:15:16.04,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,But we didn't know anything \Nabout the Titans then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.23,0:15:19.60,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting them head-on is pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.28,0:15:21.40,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,We did lose,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.40,0:15:24.82,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,but the information we gained \Ngives us hope for next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.78,0:15:30.16,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Will we abandon the tactics that cost \Ntens of thousands of lives to develop,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.16,0:15:32.21,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,and let the Titans eat us without a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.83,0:15:33.92,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.79,0:15:38.55,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I am going to exterminate all of the Titans,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.55,0:15:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and escape these cramped walls!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.84,0:15:42.47,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,That is my dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.01,0:15:46.42,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity isn't finished yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.31,0:15:55.66,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Eren!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.82,0:15:59.86,Default - italics,J,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to go outside the walls, then go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.65,0:16:02.98,Default - italics,J,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joining the Military Police, at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.25,0:16:16.30,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,Eren, when you were talking about your dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.58,0:16:18.88,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I got that from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.21,0:16:21.24,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,To live outside the walls, not inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:25.96,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joining the Survey Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.99,0:16:28.85,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious, Armin?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.85,0:16:31.80,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You got the best written test score, \Nso you should use that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.14,0:16:34.47,Default,Ar,0000,0000,0000,,I won't hold you back, even if it kills me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.84,0:16:37.57,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joining the Survey Corps, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.36,0:16:40.36,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're the valedictorian...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.36,0:16:41.73,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Join the Military Police!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.22,0:16:44.19,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,If you join the Military Police,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.67,0:16:46.56,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,then I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.46,0:16:51.19,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,If you join the Garrison, I'll join, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.12,0:16:55.61,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You'll send yourself to an early grave without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.92,0:16:58.99,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,No one asked you to do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.95,0:17:02.73,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to lose any more family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.61,0:17:26.59,Default,Townspeople,0000,0000,0000,,They're here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.59,0:17:28.56,Default,Townspeople,0000,0000,0000,,The main force of the Survey Corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.99,0:17:32.33,Default,Townspeople,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Erwin, kill the Titans for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.46,0:17:35.59,Default,Townspeople,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it's Captain Levi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.88,0:17:39.58,Default,Townspeople,0000,0000,0000,,They say he's as strong as an entire brigade.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.71,0:17:42.04,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.42,0:17:44.67,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,This is totally different than five years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.67,0:17:47.56,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many people \Nwho have high hopes for the Survey Corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.26,0:17:50.64,Default,Hanna,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's cheered up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:52.80,Default,Hanna,0000,0000,0000,,There haven't been any problems for five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.38,0:17:55.39,Default,Franz,0000,0000,0000,,And they've improved the fixed cannons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.81,0:17:58.24,Default,Franz,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the big Titans won't come again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.24,0:17:59.30,Default,Hanna,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.60,0:18:02.22,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You can't seriously believe that, \Nyou stupid lovebirds!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.22,0:18:04.93,Default,Hanna,0000,0000,0000,,You think we're a happy couple?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.93,0:18:06.39,Default,Franz,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting ahead of yourself, Eren!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.95,0:18:09.53,Default,Hannes,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.41,0:18:11.51,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Hannes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.74,0:18:15.29,Default,Hannes,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you graduated yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.72,0:18:18.04,Default,Hannes,0000,0000,0000,,Hard to believe you're the \Nlittle kids I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.25,0:18:19.96,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.96,0:18:22.45,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You've gone from a drunk to a \Ncaptain of the combat engineers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.45,0:18:23.70,Default,Ha,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.92,0:18:27.64,Default,Ha,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.64,0:18:30.04,Default,Ha,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't able to save your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.02,0:18:33.50,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't your fault, Hannes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.18,0:18:36.89,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't ignorant anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.69,0:18:39.98,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never let anything that sad happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.52,0:18:43.31,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,We will defeat the Titans.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.82,0:18:51.02,Default - italics,Hannes,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know whether to be happy \Nthat you've grown up or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.28,0:18:53.37,Default - italics,Hannes,0000,0000,0000,,Don't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.86,0:18:56.90,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.29,0:18:58.99,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You're joining the Survey Corps?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.28,0:19:02.21,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Connie, you were so eager \Nto join the Military Police!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.21,0:19:04.42,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,I was, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.04,0:19:07.84,Default,Mina,0000,0000,0000,,Your speech yesterday affected him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.19,0:19:10.14,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.60,0:19:12.81,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,It was my own decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.59,0:19:14.97,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,No need to feel embarrassed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.99,0:19:17.39,Default,To,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.52,0:19:20.70,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Thomas...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.70,0:19:21.60,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.10,0:19:23.70,Default,Sa,0000,0000,0000,,Um, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.73,0:19:28.35,Default,Sa,0000,0000,0000,,I brought meat from the officers' storehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.61,0:19:32.36,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Sasha, do you want to end up in jail?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.36,0:19:33.95,Default,Sam,0000,0000,0000,,You really are an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.95,0:19:35.44,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,Idiots are scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.81,0:19:38.32,Default,Sa,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all split it...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.32,0:19:40.64,Default,Sa,0000,0000,0000,,We can slice it and make sandwiches!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.62,0:19:42.67,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Go put it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.67,0:19:43.41,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.87,0:19:47.41,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,After all the land we lost, \Nmeat is really valuable!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.41,0:19:49.26,Default,Sa,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.80,0:19:56.89,Default,Sa,0000,0000,0000,,Once we retake the land, we can \Nraise cows and sheep again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.10,0:20:03.59,Default,Sa,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have some of the meat, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.98,0:20:06.39,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me, too! Get it ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.57,0:20:09.44,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I also will, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.03,0:20:10.97,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.78,0:20:13.36,Default,Sam,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you standing there, Eren?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.03,0:20:16.32,Default,Sam,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get back to work, or they'll find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.78,0:20:18.23,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't lunchtime yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.27,0:20:26.67,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,It's been five years since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.26,0:20:31.98,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity is finally regaining its dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.67,0:20:34.59,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,We can win!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.39,0:20:39.01,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,Our counterattack
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.56,0:20:41.61,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,has only begun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.88,0:21:03.86,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,So hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.86,0:21:05.01,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.46,0:21:13.41,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,Samuel!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:15.46,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Sasha!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.27,0:21:25.30,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,Samuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.30,0:21:26.60,Default,Co,0000,0000,0000,,don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.89,0:21:29.24,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,That was close...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.40,0:21:34.96,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,The wall has been breached?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.45,0:21:37.24,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Not again...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.72,0:21:40.73,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,The Titans will come inside the walls again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.02,0:21:48.41,Default - italics,E,0000,0000,0000,,I will annihilate all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.98,0:21:52.77,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Annihilate all of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.71,0:21:57.54,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Fixed cannon maintenance team 4,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.54,0:21:59.07,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,prepare for combat!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.45,0:22:02.90,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Our target is the Colossal Titan before us!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.46,0:22:04.42,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,This is our chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.77,0:22:06.30,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let it get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.15,0:22:17.36,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.92,0:22:20.55,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,It's been five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.58,0:23:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell has reopened its gaping maw.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.05,0:24:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no reprieve as Titans devour soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.54,0:24:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the midst of it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.96,0:24:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eren rescues Armin from death's door, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.21,0:24:10.85,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,First Battle \NBattle of Trost (1)
